docs.lead_paragraph: Michael R. Bloomberg on Friday brushed back critiques about his wealth and bristled at the suggestion that he was using it to buy success in the 2020 presidential race, arguing that other Democrats who have complained about his entry into their party’s primary could have taken it upon themselves to earn their own personal fortunes, as he had done.

headline.main: What Michael Bloomberg Said About His 2020 Rivals in a TV Interview
headline.print_headline: Bloomberg Brushes Back Rivals’ Attacks on His Wealth

docs.lead_paragraph: President Trump’s re-election campaign has run menacing and misleading ads this fall accusing Joseph R. Biden Jr. of corrupt dealings with Ukraine. Republicans in Congress are scrutinizing Mr. Biden’s son, pressing the State and Treasury Departments for information about his work for a Ukrainian energy company. The president himself has unleashed a stream of unfounded accusations against the Bidens and pushed for them to appear at a potential impeachment trial in the Senate.

headline.main: G.O.P. Tactic on Impeachment: Turn Ukraine Allegations Against Biden
